<section class="problem-section" id="problem">
  <div class="section-wrap">
    <div class="problem-grid">
      <div class="problem-text">
        <div class="section-label">The Problem</div>
        <h2 class="section-title">Silica gel is <em>everywhere</em> — and it's a problem.</h2>
        <p>Silica gel is the default desiccant found in shoes, electronics, food packaging, and more. But its production is either <strong>water-intensive</strong> or <strong>energy-intensive and toxic</strong>. Once used, nearly everyone throws it away — because no better option exists.</p>
        <p>Its main competitor, bentonite clay, comes with its own problems: toxic mining waste and heavy metal contamination. The industry needs a genuine alternative.</p>
        <div class="expert-quote">
          <p>"The concern about the environmental cost of silica gel production is real and validated at a professional level."</p>
          <cite>— Macy Zwanzig, AP Environmental Science Teacher & Redmond Environmental Sustainability Advisory Committee</cite>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div>
        <div class="stat-cards">
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="unit-label">Tons / year</span>
            <span class="big-num">200K</span>
            <div class="desc">Silica gel waste generated globally</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="unit-label">Water per kg (wet method)</span>
            <span class="big-num">40kg</span>
            <div class="desc">Water consumed to produce 1 kg of silica gel</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="unit-label">CO₂ per kg (dry method)</span>
            <span class="big-num">4.4kg</span>
            <div class="desc">Carbon emitted per kg in the dry process</div>
          </div>
          <div class="stat-card">
            <span class="unit-label">Consumers surveyed</span>
            <span class="big-num">90%</span>
            <div class="desc">Simply throw silica gel in the trash</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

